snippet.textDisplay:
I think one thing that people missed out on about this movie is the full circle resolution of the palpatine/skywalker story.
I liked how kylo was a direct descendant of a skywalker and how he gave his life at the end for ray, a descendant of a palpatine.
The skywalkers always would sacrifice themselves for the greater good, even if the person was a palpatine.
The ending focused heavily on the ancestry of the palpatines and the ancestry of the skywalkers so it was like the two becoming one in peace, hence the kiss.
Whilst kylo had a lot in common with darth vader he was vastly different from vader and acted more as a peer to ray than a father to luke and I appreciated the added complexity of their relationship.
Lastly I thought it was pretty smart to say that palpatine cloned himself because of his sith power instead of retconing it as if he had somehow survived the fall or he magically was brought back to life.
This movie is nowhere near as good as the originals because the originals were such a soulful piece of history that could've really only existed when it was released but I think JamJamAbraham did his best without fucking it up prequel style.
Although i do kind of applaud the prequels for at least doing something different.
I feel like people love to hate on the sequels because its cool to do that but they weren't abysmal, just lacking.

snippet.textDisplay:
I know I'll get down-voted to death, but I really disagree with most of what you're saying. Just saw it a few hours ago, knowing that people weren't enjoying the movie, and I thought it was pretty damn good. My biggest complaint was with that last confrontation between Rey and Palpatine just not hitting the emotional highs it needed to, and not having a very satisfying manner in which the emperor was defeated (the power of... 2 LIGHTSABERS!) I was thoroughly digging everything leading up to that though, and I was not a fan of Last Jedi, btw.


But man, after seeing all the negativity towards this shit, I thought you'd have some ACTUAL shit to point out. This is pretty much a spoiler free review, you barely talked about anything. The only spoiler is that Rey "can bring people back to life" which isn't even what happened. First, they introduce that she can HEAL wounds on that serpent. She literally fucking explains after that how she just transfers her force energy to the other person and it heals. Then, she HEALS the wound she literally just gave Kylo. THEN, Palpatine uses that shit against them to HEAL himself. I'm tired of this "the force couldn't do that before" shit. The force couldn't pull things towards you or give you mad hops until Empire, but nobody bitches about that. Also why is it a problem in the finale that there are a lot of ships when, the fucking point is that the Resistance is getting overwhelmed, and is nearly wiped out, by this new insane fleet thats been in hiding. Also also, the Star Destroyers having Death Star cannons isn't that crazy, considering in Last Jedi they describe that ramming cannon (the one Fin tried to kamikaze) using Death Star tech. Just screw it on a fucking Star Destroyer, not that crazy.


How could you forget to bitch about BB-8 rolling around all stupid like in the final shot where they tried to mimic the OG Tatooine 2 suns shot? Or the fact that Kylo and Rey fucking kissed? Or the fact that the short yellow alien chick (couldn't be fucked to remember her name) ended up not doing shit? I could write a better negative review for this movie, and I really liked it. Maybe re-watch it so you'll at least remember enough shit to bitch about.

snippet.textDisplay: I really enjoyed the movie but share all the same grievances. They just didn't bother me enough to hate it. As I was watching it, I felt happy to see what I saw, but kept feeling it was unearned. Kylo's redemption should have been a great moment, but it wasn't. It just happened, because the movie made it happen. So it's hitting all the beats I wanted as a fan, but in a way that just feels unnatural. But maybe because I'm a fan (or a sucker) I was enjoying it. Like even with the humor, I realize it feels out of place for Star Wars. It feels more like Marvel. But I still laugh. I still find it funny, even after multiple viewings. I just much rather have that humor than for it to have no humor at all.
